An Apache Lucene-based search server. 
It was developed by Shay Banon and published in 2010. 
Now maintained by Elasticsearch BV. 
Its latest version is 7.3.2 as on 24-09-2019 (Release date 12 Sep 2019)

It is a real-time distributed and open source full-text search and analytics engine. 
It is used in SPA - Single Page Application projects
It is accessible from RESTful web service interface and uses schema less JSON (JavaScript Object Notation) documents to store data. 
It is developed in Java and hence it can run on different platforms. 
It enables users to explore very large amount of data at very high speed.

It is scalable up to petabytes of structured and unstructured data. (1 petabyte = 1000000 GB)
